Packages to sort classes


Threads
- Allow processes to run in parallel.
- Was used to create a start and stop thread

Buffer Strategies
- Prevents flickering during the game
- A buffer is essentially a second 'internal' screen that the program draws to before displaying to the actual screen
- It is an internal memory

Graphics
- Graphics object was made to draw graphics to the canvas
- In Java, the coordinate system works with the y-axis being flipped (up to down is increasing)

Tick Method
- Updates the game logic as it is running

Render Method
- Updates the screen as it is running
